Th54: (for M being PseudoMetricSpace holds (for V,Q being (Element of ( M -neighbour )) holds (( ( nbourdist M ) . (V,Q) ) = ( 0 ) iff V = Q)))
proof
let M being PseudoMetricSpace;
let V being (Element of ( M -neighbour )),Q being (Element of ( M -neighbour ));
A1: (V = Q implies ( ( nbourdist M ) . (V,Q) ) = ( 0 ))
proof
consider p being (Element of M) such that A2: V = ( p -neighbour ) by CKB25:1;
A3: p in V by A2,CKB10:1;
consider q being (Element of M) such that A4: Q = ( q -neighbour ) by CKB25:1;
